{
  "text": "In summary, it has been shown that for the paraboloid front initial condition (2.4), by using the ansatz (2.5), the (3+1) dimensional PDE (2.1) is reduced to a (1+1) dimensional PDE (2.11) with variable coefficients. Similar reduced equation can be obtained by applying to the similarity reduction approaches of PDEs [CITATION_1] . to Eq. (2.1). We will denote t 0 = 1 2\u03bbc , then the term 2\u03bbc 1+2\u03bbct is written as 1 (t+t0) . Also, we will consider only \u03bb = 1; the other sign can be obtained by changingc to \u2212c.",
